@startuml
title Viaverse Job Lifecycle / Delivery Approval — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nJob workspace\nDelivery review\nStatus timeline" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nJob API\nWorkspace API" as BFF
component "JobController" as Controller
component "Job Use Cases\nStartJob\nDeliverJob\nApproveDelivery\nCancelJob" as UseCases
component "Job Policies\nparticipant authorization\npayment gate\ndelivery approval\naddress visibility" as Policies
component "Ports\nJobRepo\nOutboxPort\nPaymentStatePort\nMessagingPort" as Ports
component "payment-service\npayment authorized\npayout hold/eligible" as Payment
component "messaging-service\njob conversation\nattachments" as Messaging
database "PostgreSQL\njob\njob_delivery\njob_update\noutbox_event" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nJobStarted\nJobDelivered\nJobCompleted\nPayoutEligible" as Kafka
component "trust/review-service\nreview prompt\ntrust update later" as Trust

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Policies --> Payment : payment gate
Ports --> Messaging : conversation/context
Ports --> DB : persist
UseCases --> Kafka : events
Kafka --> Trust : review prompt

note bottom
Job use cases orchestrate work state only.
Payment capture/refund/release and dispute decisions stay in payment/dispute flows.
end note
@enduml
